The National Management if the National Assembly (NASS) has postponed the resumption of the plenary session earlier scheduled  for Tuesday, September 15 to September 29, 2020, a statement signed by the Acting Clerk to the National Assembly, Ojo Amos Olatunde Friday night has said. The NASS has been on this year’s annual recess since July 23. The statement which said the management regretted any inconveniences caused by this change of date, did not explain the reason for the shift in the resumption date, it was, however, later learned that the postponement might not be unconnected with the ongoing renovation of the NASS chambers. A staff of the NASS who preferred anonymity said the renovation cannot be completed before Tuesday, September 15, hence the shift of the resumption date to September 29